{
  "stem": "15943.5",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in the camp, they assumed he was a German child, and they gave him a birthday-- January 1.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They figured January is the first month, first day is easy to remember.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They looked at him-- ah, you look about that-- you're born 1930.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was his birthday.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then finally, later, he found out, when he came back to Poland, years later from the United States, that he was born in Lodz, and who his parents were, and that his mother's name was Minsky.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when he saw Minsky on that wall, he wanted to trace who are those Minskys.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it turned out that we are related.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he has a wonderful story that I think it should be-- I think all the stories should be told.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I'm talk-- I'm writing about his story, in connection with mine-- how we found each other.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- and sometimes, we really don't have to say anything when we talk to each other, in fact.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And his wife was born in Russia and smuggled her way out of Russia.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then she was in Israel.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he says, when I tell to her, she sometimes says things-- she doesn't understand it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When I say it to you, you know what I mean, what I'm saying.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because she says, so why didn't you do this?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Why didn't you do this?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There is something between survivors that sometimes you don't have to-- you say one word and they know what you're saying and what not to ask, or what to ask.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, so--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] Because those who deny the Holocaust-- and I had phone calls from so-called historian telling me that I'm a liar.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My books are a lie.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was no Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were no gas chambers.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
